710700f-b.text:
(1)
Eleventh Ave., east side, south from West 44th to 43rd Streets. The gasoline Estation shown on the extreme right, is at the N.E. corner of West 43rd Street. Buildings shown being 588-50 inclusive.
December 4, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
A portion of No. 1, showing only the corner buildings (Nos. 588586). Also shown is West 44th Street, east from Eleventh Ave. Excavation on the left, is at the N.E. corner.
December 4, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.
The New York Sun of January 28, 1938 carried a notice of demolition of Nos. 580 and 584. (the Third and fifth from the left, S.E. corner of 44th Street respectively). The first is the property of
the estate of Adolph D. Bendheim.
